  <mods:abstract>A view of the intersection at Penn Avenue and Stanwix Street, showing the corner of Horne's Department Store and its ornate lighting. Also visible are men on clean up detail from the 1936 flood and some residual waters. The Joseph Horne Company (known as Horne's) was founded in 1849 and closed in 1994. Architect Charles Tattersall Ingham was one of its designers.</mods:abstract>
